T1  - Straining for Shared Meaning in Organization Science: Problems of Trust and Distrust
AU  - Bigley, Gregory A.
AU  - Pearce, Jone L.
Y1  - 1998/07/01
PY  - 1998
DA  - 1998/07/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.1998.926618
DO  - 10.5465/amr.1998.926618
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 405
EP  - 421
VL  - 23
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - We present a problem-centered organizing framework of trust, in which prominent conceptualizations of trust and distrust from the organizational and allied social sciences are categorized based on the questions they attempt to answer. The framework we outline here is intended to complement earlier typologies by suggesting alternative strategies for employing the diverse trust literature, identifying questions that could be profitably addressed through interdisciplinary research efforts, and distinguishing disagreements where debate and research would seem to be especially worthwhile from those where such activities would appear to be much less useful.
AB  - We present a problem-centered organizing framework of trust, in which prominent conceptualizations of trust and distrust from the organizational and allied social sciences are categorized based on the questions they attempt to answer. The framework we outline here is intended to complement earlier typologies by suggesting alternative strategies for employing the diverse trust literature, identifying questions that could be profitably addressed through interdisciplinary research efforts, and distinguishing disagreements where debate and research would seem to be especially worthwhile from those where such activities would appear to be much less useful.
