T1  - Managers as Initiators of Trust: An Exchange Relationship Framework for Understanding Managerial Trustworthy Behavior
AU  - Whitener, Ellen M.
AU  - Brodt, Susan E.
AU  - Korsgaard, M. Audrey
AU  - Werner, Jon M.
Y1  - 1998/07/01
PY  - 1998
DA  - 1998/07/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.1998.926624
DO  - 10.5465/amr.1998.926624
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 513
EP  - 530
VL  - 23
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - In many approaches to interpersonal and organizational trust, researchers focus on employees' perceptions that their managers are trustworthy. We turn the tables, however, and examine the antecedents of managerial trustworthy behavior and the challenge of initiating trust. Drawing on agency and social exchange theories, we present an exchange relationship framework that identifies organizational, relational, and individual factors that encourage or constrain managerial trustworthy behavior.
